				"string" : "## Synopsis\n\nIn 1981, **Daniel H. H. Ingalls** published *Design Principles Behind Smalltalk* in BYTE Magazine.\nThe article articulates the conceptual and technical principles that guided the Smalltalk project at Xerox PARC, spanning language design, object model, virtual machine, user interface, and system organization.\nIt provides the clearest contemporaneous statement of Smalltalk’s foundational commitments: personal mastery, uniform object–message metaphors, automatic storage management, and language-integrated interaction.\n"
