				"string" : "## Historical Context\n\nThe Smalltalk project emerged from the Learning Research Group at Xerox PARC with the explicit goal of supporting the *creative spirit* of individual users.\nIngalls situates the work within an iterative research cycle—building systems, observing their use, redesigning the language, and rebuilding the system—explicitly likening this process to the scientific method.\n\nBy 1981, Smalltalk-80 represented the fifth full iteration of this cycle.\n"
